<p>
  
</p>
<hr>
<p>
  We're living in unique times when the direction of so many things seems up in the air. But I think there's an opportunity 
  to differentiate Basecamp even further by doing something that sounds pretty sensible&mdash;making you feel good about what you're doing. 
  That seems to be a lost art these days, doesn't it?
</p>
<p>
  Looking forward to your feedback!
</p>
